          <h3>Historical Context</h3>
          <p>The <span class="chinese-char">本命佛</span> system reflects the remarkable cultural synthesis that occurred in Tang and Song China, where Indian Buddhist theology merged with indigenous Chinese cosmological frameworks. The Earthly Branches (which predated Buddhism's arrival in China by centuries) were mapped onto Buddhist protective deities, creating a uniquely Chinese system with no equivalent in Indian Buddhism.</p>
          <p>By the Song Dynasty, specialised temples offered prayers and rituals for worshippers based on their zodiac year, and artisans produced small jade or bronze guardian deity figurines worn as personal talismans. This practice continues in modern Chinese communities worldwide.</p>
        </section>

